specs/t-011@20260408t223256z-spec.md:5:The R750 Ollama integration plan defines a `LOCAL_ONLY` runtime mode that should restrict the live daemon to the local `ollama` agent and prevent cloud-provider CLI/API usage. The current daemon only narrows `_available_agents()` when `LOCAL_ONLY` is set, which leaves multiple cloud paths open: router execution still tries to invoke a cloud CLI, direct `@claude`/`@codex`/`@gemini` dispatch can still request a cloud agent, and plan steps with an explicit cloud agent name are executed as written.
specs/t-011@20260408t223256z-spec.md:19:- If `LOCAL_ONLY=true` and a cloud agent is named explicitly in a plan step or direct dispatch, the daemon must execute `ollama` instead of the requested cloud agent.
